WEBVTT

00:00:34.722 --> 00:00:38.059
{\an8}UNDERCOVER MISS HONG

00:00:39.435 --> 00:00:41.354
And now I need an M&A expert
who can help me

00:00:41.437 --> 00:00:43.314
secure management control.

00:00:53.575 --> 00:00:55.702
REPORT ON THE STATUS
OF LARGE SHAREHOLDINGS

00:00:56.536 --> 00:00:57.495
Yeouido Pirates?

00:00:57.579 --> 00:00:59.873
I'm trying to recruit you right now,
Shin Jung-woo.

00:00:59.956 --> 00:01:01.875
Join Yeouido Pirates.

00:01:01.958 --> 00:01:04.210
First you get me kicked out of Hanmin,

00:01:04.294 --> 00:01:06.087
and now you want me to join your side?

00:01:06.171 --> 00:01:07.755
Would you, if you were me?

00:01:08.798 --> 00:01:10.091
I would, if I were you.

00:01:12.051 --> 00:01:15.722
Aren't you curious how I got the money
to buy up Hanmin stocks?

00:01:15.805 --> 00:01:18.308
How did you get it?
Did you secure a big-shot investor?

00:01:19.017 --> 00:01:22.312
That's disappointing.
Your imagination is so limited.

00:01:28.067 --> 00:01:31.070
Last summer, when I was investigating
Hanmin's slush fund,

00:01:31.154 --> 00:01:34.657
the late President Kang Myeong-hwi,
Chairman Kang Pil-beom's son,

00:01:34.741 --> 00:01:36.367
had something to give me.

00:01:42.498 --> 00:01:43.750
Keep going, will you?

00:01:44.584 --> 00:01:46.085
That was the end of the preview.

00:01:46.669 --> 00:01:48.671
Give me a straight answer
about joining me,

00:01:48.755 --> 00:01:49.881
and I'll tell you the rest.

00:01:52.258 --> 00:01:55.011
You might've gotten rid of me,
but that doesn't change a thing.

00:01:55.678 --> 00:01:57.305
Both Chairman Kang and DK Ventures

00:01:57.388 --> 00:01:59.474
will do whatever it takes to survive.

00:02:00.934 --> 00:02:03.561
This isn't a game you can win,
so just stop now.

00:02:04.145 --> 00:02:05.688
You're telling me to stand back again?

00:02:08.399 --> 00:02:10.693
This is why I'm trying to recruit you.

00:02:10.777 --> 00:02:12.987
You say it won't work,
that nothing will change,

00:02:13.071 --> 00:02:14.697
and that I shouldn't try anything.

00:02:14.781 --> 00:02:18.743
I need such terrible pieces of advice
to fuel my fighting spirit.

00:02:35.218 --> 00:02:37.929
Hong Keum-bo,
under the Yeouido Pirates' name,

00:02:38.012 --> 00:02:40.848
managed to buy up 9% of Hanmin's stocks.

00:02:42.600 --> 00:02:44.811
She dared to buy
our stocks with that money?

00:02:44.894 --> 00:02:45.770
PERSONNEL RECORD

00:02:45.853 --> 00:02:46.813
I mean,

00:02:47.397 --> 00:02:49.899
she could've lived out her whole life
with that money.

00:02:49.983 --> 00:02:51.234
Why go through the trouble?

00:02:51.317 --> 00:02:52.402
What's the point?

00:02:52.485 --> 00:02:53.736
What matters is

00:02:54.487 --> 00:02:56.823
that the chairman's slush fund is gone.

00:02:57.865 --> 00:02:58.866
Listen,

00:02:58.950 --> 00:03:02.328
we can just retrieve the money
that was stolen, all right?

00:03:02.829 --> 00:03:04.747
If we crack down hard--

00:03:04.831 --> 00:03:05.707
No.

00:03:06.290 --> 00:03:07.709
Don't act rashly.

00:03:08.626 --> 00:03:09.711
The risk is too high.

00:03:11.504 --> 00:03:14.340
Tail Hong Keum-bo and keep me updated
on her whereabouts and who she meets.

00:03:15.842 --> 00:03:18.803
I need to figure out
how many insiders are involved first.

00:03:39.866 --> 00:03:40.950
You're back late.

00:03:42.535 --> 00:03:43.828
You must be swamped at work.

00:03:44.329 --> 00:03:45.496
Mr. Oh.

00:03:45.580 --> 00:03:48.791
Do you still meet with your former
Risk Management team?

00:03:49.876 --> 00:03:50.710
Yeah, I guess.

00:03:51.377 --> 00:03:54.881
Hong Jang-mi handed in
her resignation today.

00:03:56.382 --> 00:03:57.967
Did she now?

00:03:58.051 --> 00:03:59.302
I didn't know about that.

00:04:00.136 --> 00:04:02.055
Did she submit it to Mr. Cha
from Research?

00:04:03.973 --> 00:04:05.266
Did you ever notice

00:04:05.850 --> 00:04:08.603
anything strange or suspicious about her
when she worked for you?

00:04:10.063 --> 00:04:10.897
No, I didn't.

00:04:12.607 --> 00:04:16.152
You suddenly asking me
about her is weirder, Ms. Song.

00:04:16.903 --> 00:04:19.697
Must I be questioned like this
in a home meant for rest…

00:04:21.491 --> 00:04:22.825
by someone who isn't even family?

00:04:25.870 --> 00:04:26.996
It's tiring for us both.

00:04:29.248 --> 00:04:30.083
Get some rest.

00:04:42.470 --> 00:04:44.472
Ms. Song asked me about you.

00:04:44.972 --> 00:04:46.432
She asked if anything seemed off.

00:04:46.516 --> 00:04:49.310
It means she's turning her suspicion
toward you too.

00:04:50.019 --> 00:04:51.020
Keep up the clueless act.

00:04:51.604 --> 00:04:52.438
Okay.

00:05:11.958 --> 00:05:15.002
Last summer, when I was investigating
Hanmin's slush fund,

00:05:15.086 --> 00:05:18.589
the late President Kang Myeong-hwi,
Chairman Kang Pil-beom's son,

00:05:18.673 --> 00:05:20.049
had something to give me.

00:05:23.177 --> 00:05:24.470
What did he have for her?

00:05:26.013 --> 00:05:27.432
Is it already in her possession?

00:05:42.822 --> 00:05:44.490
{\an8}So what did President Shin say?

00:05:45.575 --> 00:05:47.034
{\an8}He got all snippy.

00:05:47.952 --> 00:05:50.872
{\an8}He may be cold,
but he isn't the type to get snippy.

00:05:52.623 --> 00:05:53.457
{\an8}Wait.

00:05:54.375 --> 00:05:55.209
{\an8}Don't tell me…

00:05:56.419 --> 00:05:57.753
{\an8}Were you two…

00:05:58.337 --> 00:06:00.006
{\an8}You two are university alums.

00:06:00.923 --> 00:06:04.218
{\an8}We graduated from the same school
and were co-workers at our first job.

00:06:04.302 --> 00:06:06.429
{\an8}We were reunited at Hanmin
after nine years.

00:06:07.805 --> 00:06:08.681
{\an8}So were you two an item?

00:06:10.266 --> 00:06:11.392
{\an8}It's all in the past.

00:06:13.144 --> 00:06:16.105
{\an8}No wonder you were so confident,
even with a losing case.

00:06:16.189 --> 00:06:18.566
You clearly had an angle to work with.

00:06:19.942 --> 00:06:21.527
Enough of that outdated love story.

00:06:21.611 --> 00:06:22.987
You should quit soon too.

00:06:23.070 --> 00:06:26.282
It sounds like Ms. Song has caught on
and is pointing fingers now.

00:06:26.365 --> 00:06:27.575
Wait.

00:06:27.658 --> 00:06:30.912
If I resign too,
who will keep an eye on the 12th floor?

00:06:31.454 --> 00:06:35.458
More importantly, Ms. Song's safe
is filled with all sorts of secret intel.

00:06:37.126 --> 00:06:38.377
Oh, right.

00:06:38.461 --> 00:06:41.672
Ms. Kang has left
for Switzerland by herself.

00:06:41.756 --> 00:06:44.800
I'm still not sure whether
that clueless girl is on our side

00:06:44.884 --> 00:06:48.054
or if she'll be able
to retrieve that money for us.

00:06:49.055 --> 00:06:50.264
We'll have to wait and see.

00:06:51.599 --> 00:06:54.268
Have you heard anything
about who the next president will be?

00:06:54.352 --> 00:06:56.979
It sounded like Executive Director Oh
was deluding himself again.

00:07:07.949 --> 00:07:11.285
Is Nora still in dreamland?

00:07:11.369 --> 00:07:13.412
Nora went on a trip to Switzerland.

00:07:14.705 --> 00:07:16.749
It was just a broken engagement,
not a divorce.

00:07:16.832 --> 00:07:19.794
You could say it's a sign
of her determination to move on.

00:07:21.170 --> 00:07:22.964
{\an8}That's a bit of a stretch.

00:07:24.131 --> 00:07:26.008
Staying positive and all is good,

00:07:26.092 --> 00:07:27.385
but in a troubled time like this,

00:07:27.468 --> 00:07:30.263
traveling abroad seems a bit ill-advised.

00:07:31.639 --> 00:07:33.224
Says the wise sage.

00:07:34.517 --> 00:07:37.853
I wanted to say this
when Nora was present,

00:07:37.937 --> 00:07:39.647
but now that the president's seat
is vacant,

00:07:40.940 --> 00:07:45.152
I believe it's time we get serious
about choosing a successor.

00:07:47.530 --> 00:07:51.492
I should transfer the shares
while the stock price is down,

00:07:51.576 --> 00:07:53.619
so it reduces my tax burden.

00:07:55.329 --> 00:07:56.581
For the president's seat,

00:07:56.664 --> 00:07:58.457
I plan to promote internally

00:07:58.958 --> 00:08:00.835
rather than hire from outside.

00:08:02.003 --> 00:08:03.254
The candidates are…

00:08:05.047 --> 00:08:06.257
- Albert.
- Yes, sir.

00:08:07.049 --> 00:08:07.883
And Nora.

00:08:08.509 --> 00:08:09.719
Just the two of them.

00:08:11.137 --> 00:08:12.013
Yes, sir.

00:08:26.902 --> 00:08:28.904
There are countless men in the world,

00:08:29.447 --> 00:08:32.491
but at Hanmin Investment & Securities,

00:08:34.076 --> 00:08:35.661
{\an8}there is only one seat for the president.

00:08:35.745 --> 00:08:37.163
It's perfect for my Nora.

00:08:39.957 --> 00:08:41.167
Why Switzerland, of all places?

00:08:41.250 --> 00:08:42.585
{\an8}What?

00:08:42.668 --> 00:08:43.544
I'm talking about Ms. Kang.

00:08:47.840 --> 00:08:49.133
{\an8}Gosh.

00:08:49.216 --> 00:08:51.010
{\an8}After a breakup,
it's only natural for a woman

00:08:51.093 --> 00:08:54.639
to want to go halfway around the world,
just to be somewhere he isn't.

00:08:55.139 --> 00:08:56.140
You know?

00:08:58.643 --> 00:09:00.895
{\an8}You really know nothing
about being a woman.

00:09:01.479 --> 00:09:02.813
Besides,

00:09:02.897 --> 00:09:04.774
{\an8}Nora likes to eat.

00:09:04.857 --> 00:09:07.526
I'm sure she'll have her fill
of fondue and chocolate there.

00:09:11.656 --> 00:09:12.823
It must be a coincidence.

00:09:13.491 --> 00:09:16.327
Only the chairman and I know
about that Swiss account.

00:09:17.078 --> 00:09:18.037
But then again,

00:09:18.537 --> 00:09:21.040
even if she did know,
what could that clueless girl do?

00:09:30.675 --> 00:09:32.385
You thought you'd be president,
didn't you?

00:09:32.927 --> 00:09:35.096
Son, if you become the president,

00:09:35.179 --> 00:09:37.556
it'd be as good as me getting the job.

00:09:38.724 --> 00:09:40.184
What if Aunt Nora becomes president?

00:09:40.267 --> 00:09:41.644
Why would you even say that?

00:09:43.145 --> 00:09:45.106
Never mind the ex-grandma.

00:09:46.232 --> 00:09:47.066
What about Ms. Song?

00:09:50.152 --> 00:09:54.281
Song Ju-ran, that woman, is
the biggest thorn in our side right now.

00:09:54.865 --> 00:09:58.285
She's been meeting with
Nora's mama nonstop lately,

00:09:58.369 --> 00:10:00.871
and she's glued to the chairman's side.

00:10:02.498 --> 00:10:03.958
Ms. Song is pushing for Aunt Nora.

00:10:11.632 --> 00:10:12.717
No matter what happens,

00:10:13.259 --> 00:10:14.885
come hell or high water,

00:10:14.969 --> 00:10:17.263
you must become the new president,
understand?

00:10:18.264 --> 00:10:19.098
That way,

00:10:20.057 --> 00:10:21.976
you can help restore

00:10:22.727 --> 00:10:24.186
the shares I lost, right?

00:10:29.442 --> 00:10:31.235
We'll split the shares evenly.

00:10:31.986 --> 00:10:32.945
Yeah.

00:10:33.738 --> 00:10:34.613
Sure.

00:10:38.743 --> 00:10:40.578
{\an8}CHAIRMAN KANG PIL-BEOM

00:10:40.661 --> 00:10:43.789
{\an8}You said it'd be between
Albert and Nora during breakfast,

00:10:44.290 --> 00:10:46.333
but do you have a preference?

00:10:48.419 --> 00:10:50.463
Well, it hasn't been that long

00:10:50.963 --> 00:10:53.758
since I've had them by my side.

00:10:54.675 --> 00:10:57.219
Speaking of, do you have any thoughts?

00:10:59.513 --> 00:11:02.975
After gaining experience
in both Risk Management and Trading,

00:11:03.893 --> 00:11:07.354
Division Manager Oh does appear
to have the makings of a capable manager.

00:11:09.565 --> 00:11:12.151
On the other hand, Director Kang

00:11:13.360 --> 00:11:16.864
entered the company as a staff member
and started from the bottom.

00:11:18.073 --> 00:11:19.658
So I believe she would be

00:11:19.742 --> 00:11:21.785
more closely aligned
with your management values.

00:11:24.163 --> 00:11:25.456
Although it was brief,

00:11:26.248 --> 00:11:29.460
it was a good idea
to have her work as a staff member.

00:11:32.046 --> 00:11:34.757
How do you plan on evaluating them?

00:11:36.717 --> 00:11:39.386
I'm thinking of giving them the same task.

00:11:40.846 --> 00:11:41.889
Let's wait and see.

00:11:55.152 --> 00:11:55.986
All right.

00:11:57.530 --> 00:11:59.323
If the chairman insists,

00:12:00.449 --> 00:12:01.951
I have no other choice.

00:12:04.537 --> 00:12:06.121
His father selling his shares

00:12:06.664 --> 00:12:08.082
and his ties to Hong Keum-bo…

00:12:09.625 --> 00:12:13.712
I hold more than enough cards in my hand
to send Albert packing.

00:12:22.346 --> 00:12:23.347
HR Division?

00:12:24.056 --> 00:12:26.642
You can go ahead and process
Hong Jang-mi's resignation.

00:12:27.142 --> 00:12:29.395
Your resignation was processed.
Where are you?

00:12:30.813 --> 00:12:33.274
Shin Jung-woo insisted
on confirming it for himself.

00:12:38.028 --> 00:12:39.029
I'll call you back.

00:12:44.743 --> 00:12:46.912
It took a lot for me to show you that,

00:12:46.996 --> 00:12:47.997
just so you know.

00:12:49.790 --> 00:12:52.543
Kang Myeong-hwi, Chairman Kang's son,
was going to give you this?

00:12:53.419 --> 00:12:54.503
Yeah.

00:12:58.465 --> 00:12:59.592
What's your next target?

00:12:59.675 --> 00:13:01.927
The slush fund that's hidden
under Kang Nora's name

00:13:02.011 --> 00:13:03.137
in a Swiss account.

00:13:04.054 --> 00:13:05.389
That's asking for trouble.

00:13:05.472 --> 00:13:07.641
It's harder to bring assets in
than to move them out.

00:13:08.601 --> 00:13:11.353
Foreign currency declarations,
proof of funds, and tax audits.

00:13:11.854 --> 00:13:15.608
The tax authorities will come down on you
the moment you slip up.

00:13:15.691 --> 00:13:16.525
You know that.

00:13:16.609 --> 00:13:18.652
Kang Nora is an American citizen.

00:13:18.736 --> 00:13:20.446
She should have no issue

00:13:20.529 --> 00:13:22.865
as long as it's structured as a loan
to a Korean investment firm

00:13:22.948 --> 00:13:26.243
with the interest rate, term,
and repayment method clearly spelled out.

00:13:26.327 --> 00:13:28.078
- There will be an issue.
- No, there won't be.

00:13:28.162 --> 00:13:30.581
We're talking about 100 billion won.
How could there not be an issue?

00:13:32.541 --> 00:13:34.793
He meant 100 won, as in two 50-won coins.

00:13:37.796 --> 00:13:39.256
No need to broadcast it.

00:13:39.340 --> 00:13:41.175
This is precisely why I asked to see you.

00:13:41.258 --> 00:13:43.260
How are you so sure
that Kang Nora will take your side?

00:13:44.511 --> 00:13:46.680
Kang Nora is in Switzerland right now.

00:13:47.389 --> 00:13:48.974
Switzerland, understand?

00:14:29.223 --> 00:14:30.724
Stop playing so hard to get.

00:14:33.268 --> 00:14:35.771
Then again, this is exactly why
I want to recruit you.

00:14:36.730 --> 00:14:38.565
I need you to butt in and hit the brakes

00:14:38.649 --> 00:14:40.609
when I can't see the light has turned red.

00:15:05.217 --> 00:15:06.427
You all know who this is.

00:15:07.094 --> 00:15:08.345
He's our new member, Shin Jung-woo.

00:15:10.014 --> 00:15:10.848
I'm Shin Jung-woo.

00:15:12.141 --> 00:15:14.601
Sir, I once went
to submit a report to you.

00:15:14.685 --> 00:15:16.186
I'm currently working in the IT--

00:15:16.270 --> 00:15:17.938
Of course I remember you,

00:15:18.022 --> 00:15:18.897
Mr. Lee Yong-gi.

00:15:19.481 --> 00:15:21.567
This house suddenly feels so cramped.

00:15:21.650 --> 00:15:22.901
I wonder why.

00:15:24.069 --> 00:15:25.154
Can we trust him?

00:15:27.072 --> 00:15:28.449
You too, Ms. Go?

00:15:29.283 --> 00:15:30.701
You see, we're operating

00:15:30.784 --> 00:15:32.745
purely on trust right now,
without any contracts.

00:15:32.828 --> 00:15:33.662
I see.

00:15:33.746 --> 00:15:35.581
I also agreed to join without a contract.

00:15:36.165 --> 00:15:37.124
Why?

00:15:37.583 --> 00:15:38.667
To get revenge on my grandpa?

00:15:39.835 --> 00:15:41.420
To prevent costly mistakes.

00:15:42.004 --> 00:15:45.299
I can cover Keum-bo's legal blind spots
and emotional judgment.

00:15:45.883 --> 00:15:48.761
I guess you could call me
her rational partner.

00:15:48.844 --> 00:15:49.970
Oh my, a "partner"?

00:15:51.764 --> 00:15:53.015
A partner?

00:15:57.186 --> 00:16:01.565
To start, the funds Chairman Kang
laundered and moved offshore

00:16:01.648 --> 00:16:03.317
will be difficult to bring back.

00:16:03.859 --> 00:16:05.861
So for all of you,

00:16:05.944 --> 00:16:11.366
the only lawful, practical way
to quickly participate

00:16:11.450 --> 00:16:14.203
in the management of Hanmin…

00:16:15.454 --> 00:16:16.622
- "All of you"?
- "All of you"?

00:16:17.831 --> 00:16:18.874
Right.

00:16:18.957 --> 00:16:20.167
Let me rephrase that.

00:16:20.751 --> 00:16:22.044
All of you and I…

00:16:24.254 --> 00:16:26.048
I mean, we will…

00:16:26.131 --> 00:16:28.592
We'll be cleaning out
all the domestic slush funds.

00:16:28.675 --> 00:16:31.220
We start with borrowed-name accounts
that Seoul branch managers

00:16:31.303 --> 00:16:33.013
opened under their families.

00:16:34.723 --> 00:16:37.559
I remember thinking
how strange it was back then.

00:16:37.643 --> 00:16:40.521
- Your performance has been stellar lately.
- Thanks.

00:16:40.604 --> 00:16:42.523
I'm so envious of you.
Tell us your secret.

00:16:44.191 --> 00:16:45.651
Hello, everyone.

00:16:48.195 --> 00:16:50.155
- It's nice to see you all again.
- Hello.

00:16:50.739 --> 00:16:52.741
- Have you been well?
- Yes, ma'am. Thank you.

00:16:52.825 --> 00:16:54.910
- We've met before, right?
- Yes, it's been a while.

00:16:55.494 --> 00:16:57.454
- Nice to see you.
- You're still as beautiful as ever.

00:16:57.538 --> 00:17:00.207
- It's nice to see you again.
- Yes, nice to see you.

00:17:00.791 --> 00:17:03.043
We need to allocate some funds…

00:17:03.127 --> 00:17:05.087
The branch managers were under her thumb

00:17:05.170 --> 00:17:07.506
when she wasn't even in charge of sales.

00:17:07.589 --> 00:17:09.967
I assumed it was because
she was in the chairman's inner circle.

00:17:10.551 --> 00:17:12.261
Even when the New Korea Fund
was being sold,

00:17:12.344 --> 00:17:14.680
Chairman Kang had Ms. Song
oversee the branches.

00:17:15.264 --> 00:17:16.348
I found that odd as well.

00:17:17.349 --> 00:17:19.643
The ledger only has
the names of the branch managers

00:17:19.726 --> 00:17:20.978
and their balances,

00:17:21.562 --> 00:17:23.105
so we suspect that Song Ju-ran

00:17:23.188 --> 00:17:25.607
has the bankbooks
and seals in her possession.

00:17:27.860 --> 00:17:29.236
Ms. Song's safe.

00:17:30.195 --> 00:17:31.697
That's the gold mine.

00:17:33.031 --> 00:17:33.907
Her safe?

00:17:38.287 --> 00:17:40.164
YEOUIDO PIRATES

00:17:40.247 --> 00:17:41.707
HANMIN INVESTMENT & SECURITIES

00:17:41.790 --> 00:17:44.001
EPISODE 14: THE ERA OF GREAT PIRATES

00:18:30.589 --> 00:18:31.465
Ms. Go.

00:18:38.847 --> 00:18:40.682
I have perfect pitch.

00:18:53.862 --> 00:18:54.780
Damn.

00:19:09.419 --> 00:19:10.379
We need a key?

00:19:19.721 --> 00:19:20.847
It's open.

00:19:20.931 --> 00:19:22.224
It's open!

00:19:24.726 --> 00:19:25.560
SEALS

00:19:39.408 --> 00:19:40.242
BRANCH MANAGER

00:19:41.451 --> 00:19:42.286
SAENARA BANK

00:19:44.955 --> 00:19:45.789
VIP.

00:19:54.715 --> 00:19:55.757
{\an8}SAENARA BANK

00:20:04.349 --> 00:20:05.517
What's taking him so long?

00:20:08.770 --> 00:20:09.688
Let's see.

00:20:11.857 --> 00:20:13.942
Seals, branch managers,

00:20:14.860 --> 00:20:15.694
and VIPs.

00:20:15.777 --> 00:20:16.695
They're identical.

00:20:22.951 --> 00:20:23.785
There we go.

00:20:31.043 --> 00:20:32.169
Wait.

00:20:42.304 --> 00:20:44.097
We have the seals and the bankbooks.

00:20:44.890 --> 00:20:47.225
She even wrote down
the usernames and passwords.

00:20:47.726 --> 00:20:50.103
We just need to withdraw it all
through online banking.

00:20:51.063 --> 00:20:52.939
You wrapped it up properly, right?

00:20:53.023 --> 00:20:54.191
Of course.

00:20:54.274 --> 00:20:55.901
I'm a seasoned pro.

00:21:43.782 --> 00:21:44.783
Good.

00:21:44.866 --> 00:21:47.953
Now it's time to work your magic,
Mr. Lee and Mr. Shin.

00:21:48.912 --> 00:21:51.123
Should we start buying
as soon as the money's ready?

00:21:52.249 --> 00:21:55.252
No, we need to make the rounds
of all the Seoul branches.

00:21:55.335 --> 00:21:57.546
- That's how rumors will start.
- Okay.

00:21:58.130 --> 00:21:59.381
Why so friendly?

00:21:59.464 --> 00:22:00.465
Oh, right.

00:22:00.549 --> 00:22:01.925
We're university alums.

00:22:03.510 --> 00:22:04.761
It sounds like you were very close.

00:22:05.345 --> 00:22:06.888
Was it a sibling dynamic?

00:22:08.390 --> 00:22:10.475
Boys, focus on what I'm saying.

00:22:11.601 --> 00:22:12.644
"Boys."

00:22:14.688 --> 00:22:17.315
Now, we're going to split up the branches.

00:22:20.068 --> 00:22:22.612
SLUSH FUNDS IN BRANCHES ACROSS SEOUL

00:22:22.696 --> 00:22:23.905
{\an8}MASEOK BANK, JOGEOK BANK

00:22:23.989 --> 00:22:27.284
{\an8}NARA BANK, NONGJU BANK,
CHUNGSEO BANK, SAENARA BANK, FARMERS' BANK

00:22:27.367 --> 00:22:28.201
{\an8}ALL EMPTIED OUT

00:22:28.285 --> 00:22:30.412
HANMIN INVESTMENT & SECURITIES

00:24:07.926 --> 00:24:09.344
How's Go Bok-hee doing?

00:24:09.427 --> 00:24:11.930
She seems anxious
ever since President Shin resigned.

00:24:12.013 --> 00:24:14.891
She even combs through
the newspaper job listings during work.

00:24:16.059 --> 00:24:16.893
Is that so?

00:24:36.621 --> 00:24:37.706
I did it.

00:24:44.379 --> 00:24:46.464
Yeouido Pirates' main page is back online.

00:24:46.965 --> 00:24:48.466
Now that the server is overseas,

00:24:48.550 --> 00:24:51.344
it can't be forcibly shut down
like last time.

00:24:52.345 --> 00:24:53.305
Not a chance.

00:24:59.394 --> 00:25:03.440
YEOUIDO PIRATES
MAIN MENU, COMMUNITY, ETC.

00:25:07.610 --> 00:25:08.445
It's true.

00:25:09.738 --> 00:25:11.531
Yeouido Pirates is back.

00:25:12.490 --> 00:25:13.908
Do I have to register again?

00:25:14.826 --> 00:25:15.994
Well…

00:25:16.077 --> 00:25:19.664
I heard the head of IT was able to log in
with his old username and password.

00:25:20.165 --> 00:25:22.751
That old-school man found out before me?

00:25:26.379 --> 00:25:28.631
Ever since Mr. So and Mr. Bang left,

00:25:29.424 --> 00:25:30.467
I feel so left out.

00:25:31.718 --> 00:25:34.929
I'm too much out of the loop
when it comes to stuff like this.

00:25:35.013 --> 00:25:37.640
You should've been
looking out for me, Mr. Lee.

00:25:37.724 --> 00:25:39.517
That's why I'm here, sir.

00:25:42.520 --> 00:25:45.023
I heard people
in the IT Division talking earlier.

00:25:45.106 --> 00:25:48.234
They say rumors about someone
aggressively buying up large amounts

00:25:48.318 --> 00:25:50.403
of Hanmin stocks
are spreading like wildfire.

00:25:52.655 --> 00:25:54.115
Since the IMF crisis started,

00:25:54.199 --> 00:25:57.994
our stocks have plunged over 60%.

00:25:58.078 --> 00:25:59.788
Who would buy financial stocks

00:26:00.288 --> 00:26:01.331
when they're in free fall?

00:26:02.707 --> 00:26:04.334
- Them.
- What?

00:26:04.918 --> 00:26:07.337
{\an8}YEOUIDO PIRATES

00:26:11.383 --> 00:26:12.592
Unbelievable.

00:26:13.718 --> 00:26:15.553
HELD BY: YEOUIDO PIRATES
CEO: HONG KEUM-BO

00:26:27.732 --> 00:26:29.984
This Yeouido Pirates business.

00:26:30.068 --> 00:26:33.988
Shin Jung-woo shut this down last time,
didn't he?

00:26:34.739 --> 00:26:35.615
Yes, sir.

00:26:35.698 --> 00:26:38.284
We shut down
the PC communication community,

00:26:38.868 --> 00:26:41.913
but it appears they have established
an independent website.

00:26:43.206 --> 00:26:44.457
These bastards

00:26:45.250 --> 00:26:47.585
even set up an investment trust company,

00:26:47.669 --> 00:26:50.380
and now they're buying up
our company stocks?

00:26:51.297 --> 00:26:53.508
And who is this Hong Keum-bo

00:26:53.591 --> 00:26:55.176
listed as their CEO?

00:26:55.969 --> 00:26:58.012
I believe they're the leader
of Yeouido Pirates.

00:26:58.596 --> 00:26:59.431
Its captain.

00:27:00.056 --> 00:27:00.890
"Captain"?

00:27:00.974 --> 00:27:05.395
Yes, their nickname is
"The Captain" in the community.

00:27:05.478 --> 00:27:06.521
What a clown, right?

00:27:06.604 --> 00:27:10.108
Their name only surfaced
after the company was registered.

00:27:11.776 --> 00:27:13.111
Good grief.

00:27:22.871 --> 00:27:24.038
Listen carefully.

00:27:25.290 --> 00:27:26.166
Between Albert

00:27:26.749 --> 00:27:27.584
and Nora,

00:27:28.209 --> 00:27:29.294
I will appoint

00:27:29.961 --> 00:27:33.047
whoever catches the Captain first

00:27:33.131 --> 00:27:35.258
as the president.

00:27:45.143 --> 00:27:46.644
How dare they…

00:27:53.735 --> 00:27:54.986
Yahoo!

00:27:55.069 --> 00:27:57.489
Son, if we just catch Yeouido Pirates,

00:27:57.572 --> 00:27:59.115
the president's seat will be yours.

00:28:00.074 --> 00:28:00.950
President Oh.

00:28:02.660 --> 00:28:03.578
Dad.

00:28:03.661 --> 00:28:05.455
We're nowhere close to finding them.

00:28:06.164 --> 00:28:07.207
It's just a matter of time.

00:28:07.957 --> 00:28:11.252
I'll utilize all my connections
and intel networks

00:28:11.336 --> 00:28:14.005
to make you the president, okay?

00:28:16.508 --> 00:28:17.342
Okay.

00:28:18.927 --> 00:28:21.429
Remember, Captain Hook
was defeated by Peter Pan.

00:28:24.599 --> 00:28:26.434
Shin Jung-woo.

00:28:27.018 --> 00:28:28.686
DK Ventures.

00:28:30.396 --> 00:28:33.274
And now Yeouido Pirates.

00:28:34.150 --> 00:28:37.612
Is Hanmin surrounded by hostile forces,

00:28:38.279 --> 00:28:39.739
just waiting to strike?

00:28:42.075 --> 00:28:43.368
I'm telling you,

00:28:43.451 --> 00:28:46.329
they're trying to take what's not theirs
without even lifting a finger.

00:28:48.373 --> 00:28:50.166
You're still going strong.

00:28:50.667 --> 00:28:53.211
This could all blow over
without much trouble, like last time.

00:28:54.087 --> 00:28:55.213
But you know,

00:28:56.089 --> 00:28:58.341
that name, Hong Keum-bo…

00:28:59.759 --> 00:29:03.096
I've heard that name somewhere before.

00:29:06.015 --> 00:29:07.267
I'll look into it.

00:29:08.226 --> 00:29:09.060
All right.

00:29:18.069 --> 00:29:19.153
Here.

00:29:23.324 --> 00:29:25.827
You look awfully glum
for the sole survivor.

00:29:25.910 --> 00:29:27.871
Do you have the world on your shoulders?

00:29:27.954 --> 00:29:28.788
They're so droopy.

00:29:29.455 --> 00:29:30.290
Understaffed.

00:29:30.373 --> 00:29:31.457
Overworked.

00:29:31.541 --> 00:29:32.834
Stressed.

00:29:33.543 --> 00:29:35.712
All the employees
are working themselves to the bone,

00:29:35.795 --> 00:29:36.796
but the higher-ups

00:29:36.880 --> 00:29:39.382
are throwing everything they have
into the succession battle.

00:29:39.966 --> 00:29:42.886
Well, the chairman despises taxes.

00:29:43.678 --> 00:29:46.180
The mere mention of them,
and he'd call the country a thief.

00:29:46.806 --> 00:29:48.141
I'm sure he's trying
to transfer the shares

00:29:48.224 --> 00:29:51.394
when the stock price has dropped
to save on inheritance tax.

00:29:52.437 --> 00:29:55.481
At this rate, Albert might really
become the president.

00:29:56.691 --> 00:29:59.068
Speaking of which,
maybe I should've invited Big Al too?

00:29:59.152 --> 00:30:00.778
Oh, and Hong Jang-mi.

00:30:00.862 --> 00:30:02.822
I heard Ms. Hong
was transferred to Research.

00:30:02.906 --> 00:30:04.115
How is she doing?

00:30:04.198 --> 00:30:07.035
Ms. Hong held out
during the second restructuring,

00:30:08.036 --> 00:30:09.162
but she ended up quitting.

00:30:11.623 --> 00:30:14.834
She really went out of her way
to make life difficult for herself.

00:30:18.546 --> 00:30:19.380
Hello?

00:30:20.381 --> 00:30:21.633
Yes, Executive Director Oh!

00:30:24.093 --> 00:30:24.928
Yes.

00:30:26.846 --> 00:30:28.473
How have you been doing, Bang?

00:30:29.641 --> 00:30:32.060
Are you looking for a new job?

00:30:33.686 --> 00:30:35.313
I've submitted my résumé everywhere,

00:30:36.230 --> 00:30:37.148
but it hasn't been easy.

00:30:39.943 --> 00:30:41.694
Times are tough.

00:30:43.071 --> 00:30:45.239
I mean, all my kids are all grown up,

00:30:46.324 --> 00:30:48.242
so I can live off of my savings.

00:30:48.743 --> 00:30:51.371
But you're still
in your prime years right now.

00:30:53.748 --> 00:30:57.168
I could check if any smaller
financial institutions are hiring for you.

00:30:57.251 --> 00:31:01.381
No, I don't want to be
handling money anymore.

00:31:06.552 --> 00:31:08.930
See that? It's like I'm always on call.

00:31:10.014 --> 00:31:11.391
Come on,

00:31:11.474 --> 00:31:14.727
how the hell am I supposed to find
the Captain of Yeouido Pirates?

00:31:15.353 --> 00:31:16.562
If I had such talents,

00:31:16.646 --> 00:31:18.648
I would've left Yeouido years ago!

00:31:21.109 --> 00:31:23.653
- Have a drink.
- No, I have to work early tomorrow.

00:31:25.238 --> 00:31:26.614
I told you.

00:31:26.698 --> 00:31:28.449
You should've fired Ms. Hong back then.

00:31:28.533 --> 00:31:31.452
Why in the world
did you sacrifice yourself, Bang?

00:31:34.080 --> 00:31:35.915
Look at you, laughing it off again.

00:31:38.501 --> 00:31:39.419
Damn it.

00:31:42.338 --> 00:31:45.466
Get your gimbap here.

00:31:46.718 --> 00:31:49.512
{\an8}They're 1,000 won each.

00:31:49.595 --> 00:31:50.638
{\an8}BLOWOUT SALE

00:31:58.104 --> 00:32:00.523
Ms. Hong held out
during the second restructuring,

00:32:00.606 --> 00:32:01.983
but she ended up quitting.

00:32:03.276 --> 00:32:05.695
She really went out of her way
to make life difficult for herself.

00:32:10.324 --> 00:32:11.200
I'll take a gimbap.

00:32:12.785 --> 00:32:13.661
Excuse me.

00:32:15.038 --> 00:32:16.873
- Sir!
- Yes?

00:32:16.956 --> 00:32:18.041
One gimbap, please.

00:32:18.124 --> 00:32:19.876
{\an8}Sure. That'll be 1,000 won.

00:32:20.460 --> 00:32:22.503
All right. Thank you.

00:32:37.477 --> 00:32:38.394
Gimbap for sale.

00:32:40.646 --> 00:32:41.522
Thank you.

00:32:41.606 --> 00:32:42.690
- Thank you.
- Goodbye.

00:32:44.484 --> 00:32:47.111
It's late. Go home with Bom.

00:32:49.822 --> 00:32:50.823
I'll close up with you.

00:32:50.907 --> 00:32:52.533
You're back at work tomorrow.

00:32:52.617 --> 00:32:55.036
It's a long commute to Seoul,
so you need your sleep.

00:32:55.119 --> 00:32:56.204
I don't think I can sleep.

00:32:58.331 --> 00:32:59.290
You know,

00:32:59.373 --> 00:33:02.251
it's really nice having you around
and helping us out.

00:33:02.335 --> 00:33:05.296
If work gets too tough,
you can always open a sister chicken shop.

00:33:05.379 --> 00:33:08.299
I'll give you a great deal
on the secret recipe.

00:33:08.382 --> 00:33:09.926
You've got some nerve.

00:33:13.096 --> 00:33:15.056
I saw a nice storefront for rent recently.

00:33:16.224 --> 00:33:17.141
It's close by.

00:33:18.059 --> 00:33:20.269
I'm being serious. Think about it, okay?

00:33:23.815 --> 00:33:26.150
HANMIN INVESTMENT & SECURITIES
MAGANG BRANCH

00:33:31.405 --> 00:33:33.282
Let's have another productive day today.

00:33:33.366 --> 00:33:35.409
- Yes, sir.
- Let's get ready to open.

00:33:41.624 --> 00:33:42.959
She's really something else.

00:33:43.042 --> 00:33:44.335
I wouldn't come back if I were her.

00:33:44.418 --> 00:33:46.254
No branch manager
would be happy to see her.

00:33:46.337 --> 00:33:47.672
She was a total nuisance.

00:33:48.256 --> 00:33:49.966
Did you hear about the settlement she got?

00:33:50.049 --> 00:33:51.259
- Really?
- Yeah.

00:33:52.176 --> 00:33:53.261
Who told you that?

00:33:54.137 --> 00:33:57.014
I didn't get a single cent.

00:34:10.695 --> 00:34:12.738
Why can't you do it?

00:34:12.822 --> 00:34:15.783
You said you could before,
so you should do it now.

00:34:15.867 --> 00:34:18.077
Are you kidding me right now, huh?

00:34:18.161 --> 00:34:19.245
Do you think I'm a joke?

00:34:19.328 --> 00:34:20.454
I'm really sorry, ma'am.

00:34:20.538 --> 00:34:21.998
I got all the documents
you told me to get!

00:34:22.081 --> 00:34:24.292
I will sue you!

00:34:26.752 --> 00:34:29.630
Get me the branch manager right now.

00:34:30.631 --> 00:34:33.801
You said I could get the loan before,
so give me the loan now.

00:34:33.885 --> 00:34:36.095
This young lady says I can't!

00:34:36.179 --> 00:34:38.514
Hurry up and check. Now!

00:34:39.807 --> 00:34:41.392
Where are you going?

00:34:41.976 --> 00:34:43.060
Ma'am.

00:34:43.686 --> 00:34:44.770
Let me show you to my office.

00:34:45.354 --> 00:34:48.691
No, I'd like Ms. Kim Mi-sook
to handle my account.

00:34:50.860 --> 00:34:52.403
{\an8}Can you deposit this as available funds?

00:35:03.206 --> 00:35:04.123
Did you see

00:35:04.749 --> 00:35:07.960
how the branch manager's face lit up
with each stack I pulled out?

00:35:09.003 --> 00:35:10.963
All I did was
deposit the money you brought,

00:35:11.047 --> 00:35:13.049
but I feel like
I already earned my keep today.

00:35:13.132 --> 00:35:16.344
The branch manager actually smiled
when he sent me off for lunch.

00:35:18.262 --> 00:35:21.641
It's just money that won't sit for long
before it's used to buy stocks.

00:35:24.143 --> 00:35:26.312
Are your coworkers giving you a hard time?

00:35:29.440 --> 00:35:32.401
Everyone was happy to see me
and welcomed me back.

00:35:34.153 --> 00:35:35.988
I'm ready to start working hard again.

00:35:38.741 --> 00:35:40.326
You don't have to try too hard.

00:35:42.745 --> 00:35:44.413
I learned that if you try too hard,

00:35:44.497 --> 00:35:46.207
you end up feeling wronged at some point.

00:35:50.002 --> 00:35:54.423
But you're also working hard on something.

00:35:55.716 --> 00:35:57.301
I hope it works out for you.

00:35:59.345 --> 00:36:01.305
I hope that for me too.

00:36:04.475 --> 00:36:05.393
Eat up.

00:36:33.004 --> 00:36:33.963
Hello?

00:36:35.548 --> 00:36:36.716
Okay, we'll be right down.

00:36:42.346 --> 00:36:44.932
Big Al and Ms. Go
are waiting for us at the restaurant.

00:36:45.016 --> 00:36:46.517
- Takeout for me, please.
- Takeout for me, please.

00:36:48.644 --> 00:36:50.604
Okay, I'll pick up two servings.

00:36:55.276 --> 00:36:56.277
Why is it just you?

00:36:57.028 --> 00:36:59.488
Captain Hong and President Shin
asked for takeout.

00:37:04.827 --> 00:37:05.661
They're so similar.

00:37:06.245 --> 00:37:08.831
Their work styles, focus,
and even their approach to life.

00:37:09.415 --> 00:37:10.833
They used to be a couple, after all.

00:37:16.672 --> 00:37:17.840
- A couple?
- What?

00:37:17.923 --> 00:37:18.758
For how long?

00:37:18.841 --> 00:37:21.719
I'm not sure how long it lasted,
but they broke up nine years ago.

00:37:22.303 --> 00:37:23.137
Nine years…

00:37:24.263 --> 00:37:26.474
Then there's nothing to worry about.

00:37:26.974 --> 00:37:28.225
I still have a chance.

00:37:29.185 --> 00:37:30.519
Who are you trying to beat?

00:37:31.187 --> 00:37:33.397
The dumbfounded Mr. Lee Yong-gi here?

00:37:33.481 --> 00:37:35.024
That's why they were so friendly.

00:37:35.107 --> 00:37:36.609
I see now.

00:37:36.692 --> 00:37:38.861
Their work styles, focus…

00:37:39.445 --> 00:37:42.031
That's why they were so similar. I see…

00:37:43.574 --> 00:37:46.160
Let's forget this side quest
and focus on the main one.

00:37:46.744 --> 00:37:48.579
Especially you, future President Al.

00:37:59.757 --> 00:38:01.926
Tell your father at his office tomorrow

00:38:02.009 --> 00:38:04.095
that you found
the Captain of Yeouido Pirates.

00:38:18.943 --> 00:38:21.195
Come on now, Mr. Nam.

00:38:21.278 --> 00:38:23.864
The Financial Supervisory Service
must have

00:38:23.948 --> 00:38:26.867
some kind of internal insight
on Yeouido Pirates.

00:38:27.368 --> 00:38:28.619
Yeah.

00:38:28.702 --> 00:38:31.288
They're spreading information
that disrupts the market,

00:38:31.789 --> 00:38:33.124
and you'll just let them be?

00:38:34.250 --> 00:38:35.251
Come on now.

00:38:35.793 --> 00:38:39.797
This "Captain" or whatever
needs to be captured for the public good.

00:38:40.464 --> 00:38:41.340
Come on, tell me.

00:38:41.424 --> 00:38:43.008
You must know something.

00:38:45.719 --> 00:38:46.929
What are you doing?

00:38:47.012 --> 00:38:48.055
You punk.

00:38:48.639 --> 00:38:51.308
Can't you see I'm working my tail off
to make you president?

00:38:51.392 --> 00:38:52.226
Dad.

00:38:54.353 --> 00:38:55.980
The Captain of Yeouido Pirates.

00:38:57.440 --> 00:38:58.274
I know who it is.

00:38:58.357 --> 00:38:59.567
You do?

00:38:59.650 --> 00:39:01.777
Well, who is it? Tell me.

00:39:09.243 --> 00:39:11.120
- Oh A-ram.
- Oh A-ram?

00:39:11.203 --> 00:39:12.288
Oh A-ram, that punk…

00:39:15.458 --> 00:39:17.293
Wait, but you're Oh A-ram.

00:39:18.294 --> 00:39:19.211
That's your Korean name.

00:39:21.755 --> 00:39:22.590
Right.

00:39:24.592 --> 00:39:25.468
I am…

00:39:26.427 --> 00:39:27.261
the Captain.

00:39:34.018 --> 00:39:35.311
You damn punk.

00:39:37.563 --> 00:39:38.397
Why the hell…

00:39:39.607 --> 00:39:42.401
- Wait!
- Why the hell would you do that? Why?

00:39:42.485 --> 00:39:43.611
Come on now.

00:39:43.694 --> 00:39:45.321
Just hold on! Stop.

00:39:46.280 --> 00:39:48.199
You're the one
who dragged me back to Korea!

00:39:48.282 --> 00:39:49.825
I did it because I was bored.

00:39:53.162 --> 00:39:54.622
Are you all right, sir?

00:39:56.248 --> 00:39:57.917
I'm sure he'll be mad,

00:39:58.000 --> 00:39:59.877
but he'll have no choice
but to find a Plan B.

00:39:59.960 --> 00:40:03.297
Because no one can know
that you're the Captain, Albert.

00:40:05.132 --> 00:40:07.676
Oh, we were just bored.

00:40:09.345 --> 00:40:10.930
It's a family matter. Get back to work.

00:40:11.847 --> 00:40:12.932
Yes, sir.

00:40:13.015 --> 00:40:14.433
Let's go.

00:40:19.980 --> 00:40:22.316
- You call yourself my son?
- Wait!

00:40:23.025 --> 00:40:23.984
Wait a minute.

00:40:26.946 --> 00:40:31.408
Yeouido Pirates bought up
Hanmin stocks, right?

00:40:32.243 --> 00:40:33.410
Then they belong to us.

00:40:36.664 --> 00:40:39.124
Where did you get such an investment?

00:40:39.917 --> 00:40:41.168
You had the money?

00:40:41.710 --> 00:40:44.797
Shouldn't you be angry at me right now?

00:40:45.506 --> 00:40:46.340
No.

00:40:46.924 --> 00:40:47.925
Not at all.

00:40:49.885 --> 00:40:51.303
This is excellent news!

00:40:51.387 --> 00:40:52.304
We must remain calm.

00:40:52.888 --> 00:40:55.432
If the chairman finds out about this,

00:40:55.516 --> 00:40:59.103
he'll blow a fuse and accuse us
of scheming behind his back.

00:40:59.687 --> 00:41:01.272
Yes, Dad. That's precisely right.

00:41:01.355 --> 00:41:02.606
Don't worry.

00:41:03.399 --> 00:41:04.733
No problem.

00:41:06.485 --> 00:41:08.362
Your dad will take care of this.

00:41:10.447 --> 00:41:12.157
Damn it. Why isn't this thing working?

00:41:20.833 --> 00:41:23.377
PERSONAL INFORMATION FORM

00:41:32.136 --> 00:41:33.554
According to my research,

00:41:33.637 --> 00:41:35.514
the real Captain is Korean-Japanese.

00:41:36.807 --> 00:41:39.184
He used a proxy to form a company in Korea

00:41:39.268 --> 00:41:41.061
to buy up the shares.

00:41:52.406 --> 00:41:53.616
Are you certain?

00:41:56.869 --> 00:41:58.078
Forgive me,

00:41:59.163 --> 00:42:00.497
but you share some of the blame, sir.

00:42:01.290 --> 00:42:02.124
What?

00:42:04.168 --> 00:42:06.086
With the president's seat remaining vacant

00:42:06.879 --> 00:42:10.341
and your heirs still too young,
opportunists are circling from all sides.

00:42:11.592 --> 00:42:12.426
Sir.

00:42:13.677 --> 00:42:15.804
Even if you can't trust me,
please trust Albert.

00:42:16.680 --> 00:42:19.767
He's still better than Nora, isn't he?

00:42:25.606 --> 00:42:28.567
I guess I should keep my word.

00:42:37.326 --> 00:42:39.078
{\an8}PRESIDENT ALBERT OH

00:42:41.580 --> 00:42:43.707
"Oh Albert."

00:42:45.959 --> 00:42:46.794
It suits you.

00:42:48.379 --> 00:42:49.213
Are you happy?

00:42:49.296 --> 00:42:51.799
Oh, happy doesn't even
begin to explain it.

00:42:52.508 --> 00:42:55.552
Even one day in that president's seat

00:42:55.636 --> 00:42:56.887
makes a world of difference.

00:42:58.514 --> 00:43:02.935
I knew taking care of all this
before Nora came back

00:43:03.018 --> 00:43:05.020
was clearly the way to go.

00:43:05.979 --> 00:43:07.898
I saw on Yeouido Pirates

00:43:07.981 --> 00:43:10.818
that they call you
Oh Deok-gyu the Shadow Ruler.

00:43:12.861 --> 00:43:14.988
Those punks sure are witty.

00:43:15.072 --> 00:43:16.865
They're all just jealous.

00:43:17.449 --> 00:43:21.370
You know, your dad
had to plant countless alibis

00:43:21.453 --> 00:43:26.500
in every outlet imaginable
to trick the ever-distrustful chairman.

00:43:26.583 --> 00:43:28.293
You have no idea.

00:43:29.294 --> 00:43:30.629
Now, my son.

00:43:32.381 --> 00:43:33.465
Just trust me.

00:43:34.049 --> 00:43:34.883
Got it?

00:43:40.889 --> 00:43:41.932
My handsome son.

00:43:48.063 --> 00:43:50.149
HANMIN INVESTMENT & SECURITIES

00:44:06.498 --> 00:44:10.043
Can't you see I'm working my tail off
to make you president?

00:44:10.127 --> 00:44:10.961
Dad.

00:44:11.545 --> 00:44:12.755
The Captain of Yeouido Pirates.

00:44:13.881 --> 00:44:14.715
I know who it is.

00:44:15.549 --> 00:44:16.592
You do?

00:44:16.675 --> 00:44:18.469
Well, who is it? Tell me.

00:44:19.803 --> 00:44:21.597
- Oh A-ram.
- Oh A-ram?

00:44:21.680 --> 00:44:22.931
Oh A-ram, that punk…

00:44:23.682 --> 00:44:25.851
Wait, but you're Oh A-ram.

00:44:25.934 --> 00:44:27.311
That's your Korean name.

00:44:28.061 --> 00:44:29.188
Right.

00:44:29.855 --> 00:44:30.689
I am…

00:44:31.648 --> 00:44:32.483
the Captain.

00:44:40.657 --> 00:44:41.617
Hold on.

00:44:42.493 --> 00:44:44.244
What are you talking about?

00:44:44.745 --> 00:44:47.998
Albert is what now, exactly?

00:44:48.081 --> 00:44:49.374
Albert is…

00:44:50.709 --> 00:44:52.920
the one you ordered them to find, sir.

00:44:53.837 --> 00:44:55.005
The Captain…

00:44:56.048 --> 00:44:57.299
of Yeouido Pirates.

00:44:58.675 --> 00:44:59.635
Unbelievable.

00:45:00.385 --> 00:45:02.095
Look here.

00:45:02.179 --> 00:45:05.891
{\an8}I thoroughly assessed everything
and completed due diligence

00:45:05.974 --> 00:45:09.853
before I decided to
appoint Albert as president!

00:45:09.937 --> 00:45:10.938
It seems

00:45:11.647 --> 00:45:14.358
that Executive Director Oh deceived you

00:45:15.025 --> 00:45:16.568
to make Albert the president.

00:45:16.652 --> 00:45:18.654
Good grief.

00:45:19.279 --> 00:45:21.323
My goodness.

00:45:27.621 --> 00:45:28.455
Oh A-ram.

00:45:29.164 --> 00:45:30.040
I am…

00:45:31.333 --> 00:45:32.209
the Captain.

00:45:33.835 --> 00:45:36.588
If the chairman finds out about this,

00:45:36.672 --> 00:45:40.467
he'll blow a fuse and accuse us
of scheming behind his back.

00:45:41.552 --> 00:45:43.303
Yes, Dad. That's precisely right.

00:45:43.387 --> 00:45:44.513
Don't worry.

00:45:45.305 --> 00:45:46.765
No problem.

00:45:46.848 --> 00:45:49.142
Your dad will take care of this.

00:45:53.355 --> 00:45:54.731
That's not all.

00:45:56.525 --> 00:45:57.943
Recently,

00:45:59.069 --> 00:46:03.031
Executive Director Oh sold off
his nine percent stake in the company.

00:46:04.199 --> 00:46:05.367
And

00:46:05.450 --> 00:46:09.037
the slush fund
hidden under the OW was looted.

00:46:10.455 --> 00:46:11.999
I've confirmed Executive Director Oh

00:46:13.292 --> 00:46:14.126
was behind it.

00:46:15.961 --> 00:46:17.838
Oh Deok-gyu!

00:46:25.220 --> 00:46:27.389
What he did was incredibly immature.

00:46:29.141 --> 00:46:30.684
He regrets his actions deeply.

00:46:31.268 --> 00:46:32.644
I should've taught him better.

00:46:33.312 --> 00:46:34.688
Please forgive him, just this once.

00:46:34.771 --> 00:46:35.689
Do you think

00:46:36.648 --> 00:46:39.693
I'm this upset
about some internet foolery?

00:46:40.986 --> 00:46:42.237
You!

00:46:42.321 --> 00:46:44.364
Where did you sell off

00:46:44.948 --> 00:46:46.825
your nine percent stake in the company?

00:46:47.618 --> 00:46:48.619
That's…

00:46:49.411 --> 00:46:50.454
Not only that,

00:46:51.538 --> 00:46:54.249
you even touched the slush fund?

00:46:54.750 --> 00:46:55.834
A slush fund?

00:46:56.460 --> 00:46:58.170
I really don't know
anything about that, sir.

00:46:58.253 --> 00:46:59.630
- You don't?
- No.

00:47:00.297 --> 00:47:01.131
What's going on?

00:47:02.257 --> 00:47:05.302
Explain to me
what happened to your shares first!

00:47:09.389 --> 00:47:10.307
I screwed up.

00:47:11.350 --> 00:47:12.434
Be quiet.

00:47:12.517 --> 00:47:14.436
You stop it, Dad.

00:47:15.020 --> 00:47:16.730
You think Grandpa will go broke over that?

00:47:16.813 --> 00:47:17.898
You think we will?

00:47:24.279 --> 00:47:26.239
If you're curious
about the shares he sold,

00:47:27.491 --> 00:47:29.076
then answer my question first.

00:47:32.663 --> 00:47:33.997
Uncle Myeong-hwi's car accident…

00:47:35.791 --> 00:47:36.958
You instigated it, didn't you?

00:47:39.336 --> 00:47:40.420
What did you just say?

00:47:40.504 --> 00:47:42.923
He was trying to get you
to cooperate in the slush fund probe.

00:47:44.216 --> 00:47:47.177
You considered that a betrayal
and killed him off, didn't you?

00:47:47.260 --> 00:47:48.804
Why you little…

00:47:59.189 --> 00:48:01.233
What's the point of having family

00:48:02.234 --> 00:48:05.612
when they're all seeking their chance
to stab me in the back?

00:48:07.030 --> 00:48:08.365
Both of you!

00:48:08.949 --> 00:48:10.617
Get out of my sight.

00:48:10.701 --> 00:48:12.703
Right now, you bastards!

00:48:13.245 --> 00:48:14.079
Sir.

00:48:16.164 --> 00:48:18.083
- I know nothing about the slush fund--
- Let go!

00:48:18.166 --> 00:48:19.084
Father!

00:48:19.584 --> 00:48:21.795
You know me.
This is a grave misunderstanding!

00:48:22.295 --> 00:48:24.631
I swear I know nothing
about the slush fund!

00:48:25.340 --> 00:48:26.466
Chairman!

00:48:27.551 --> 00:48:29.553
Oh god…

00:48:43.024 --> 00:48:43.859
We've…

00:48:45.485 --> 00:48:47.446
been played by that woman, Song Ju-ran.

00:48:48.697 --> 00:48:50.991
She waited for you to become president,

00:48:51.491 --> 00:48:52.826
and then set off that bomb…

00:48:54.619 --> 00:48:56.121
to get rid of us in one go.

00:48:58.290 --> 00:48:59.624
You knew about it, didn't you?

00:49:01.626 --> 00:49:03.044
That Uncle Myeong-hwi's accident

00:49:04.629 --> 00:49:05.839
wasn't really an accident.

00:49:08.633 --> 00:49:09.968
Isn't that why…

00:49:11.887 --> 00:49:13.597
you threw that punch in front of Grandpa?

00:49:17.642 --> 00:49:19.770
What does it matter
if it was an accident or not?

00:49:22.022 --> 00:49:24.316
We only got our chance
because Kang Myeong-hwi died.

00:49:30.405 --> 00:49:33.200
Even if I'd won Grandpa's favor
and things had worked out…

00:49:35.285 --> 00:49:37.245
I'd have ended up like Uncle Myeong-hwi.

00:49:38.497 --> 00:49:40.832
We should be thankful
we were kicked out and not killed.

00:49:44.127 --> 00:49:44.961
My son.

00:49:46.588 --> 00:49:49.216
We still have those
Yeouido Pirates shares.

00:49:49.800 --> 00:49:50.759
Right?

00:49:50.842 --> 00:49:51.760
Those are ours.

00:49:52.636 --> 00:49:55.222
If we use that as a stepping stone
and bide our time--

00:49:55.305 --> 00:49:56.890
They don't belong to us!

00:49:58.225 --> 00:49:59.184
Please.

00:50:00.477 --> 00:50:01.561
Please just stop.

00:50:17.244 --> 00:50:18.286
They're not ours?

00:50:41.226 --> 00:50:42.269
Who is it?

00:50:44.813 --> 00:50:45.939
Your plan worked, Captain Hong.

00:50:46.648 --> 00:50:47.482
We got kicked out.

00:50:49.276 --> 00:50:50.110
Come in.

00:50:54.239 --> 00:50:58.118
Ms. Song framed my dad
for the missing OW slush fund too.

00:50:59.202 --> 00:51:00.495
That wasn't a part of the plan.

00:51:01.997 --> 00:51:06.251
That means Ms. Song
still hasn't told the chairman

00:51:06.334 --> 00:51:08.128
about Hong Keum-bo and Hong Jang-mi.

00:51:10.964 --> 00:51:11.798
Are you okay?

00:51:14.134 --> 00:51:14.968
I don't know.

00:51:15.594 --> 00:51:16.845
I'm officially penniless now,

00:51:16.928 --> 00:51:19.681
so you're responsible for me now,
whichever identity you take on.

00:51:21.266 --> 00:51:23.101
I don't have a cent to my name now.

00:51:23.184 --> 00:51:24.060
Call me Penniless Al.

00:51:24.144 --> 00:51:25.353
She'd better take care of me.

00:51:31.234 --> 00:51:32.402
ELIMINATING CHAIRMAN KANG PIL-BEOM'S
INNER CIRCLE

00:51:32.485 --> 00:51:34.529
{\an8}STEP 2: ALBERT OH, OH DEOK-GYU

00:51:34.613 --> 00:51:39.159
{\an8}ALBERT OH: ON OUR SIDE
OH DEOK-GYU: ELIMINATED

00:51:41.870 --> 00:51:43.079
Welcome back.

00:51:43.163 --> 00:51:43.997
Hello.

00:51:45.665 --> 00:51:47.042
Nora!

00:51:47.125 --> 00:51:48.877
Why didn't you answer my calls?

00:51:49.461 --> 00:51:51.796
Oh Deok-gyu and Albert
were kicked out of the house.

00:51:51.880 --> 00:51:53.173
The chairman made them leave.

00:51:53.798 --> 00:51:54.633
Why?

00:51:55.342 --> 00:51:58.345
They sold off company shares
and even touched the company funds.

00:51:59.179 --> 00:52:00.347
Oh my gosh.

00:52:00.430 --> 00:52:02.015
"Oh my gosh," indeed!

00:52:04.601 --> 00:52:05.936
Hey, where are you going?

00:52:07.145 --> 00:52:08.521
The office to say hi to Dad.

00:52:09.648 --> 00:52:11.942
Wait here so I can go with you.
Let me get changed.

00:52:19.199 --> 00:52:22.118
I just received word
that Ms. Kang has returned.

00:52:22.202 --> 00:52:24.788
I was worried she'd still be heartbroken
about the engagement,

00:52:24.871 --> 00:52:26.581
but I hear she returned in high spirits.

00:52:27.374 --> 00:52:30.335
She's on her way here to say hello to you.

00:52:31.211 --> 00:52:33.254
I could just see her at home.

00:52:35.799 --> 00:52:36.758
Ms. Song.

00:52:37.634 --> 00:52:38.843
Is there

00:52:39.886 --> 00:52:41.471
anything else…

00:52:43.431 --> 00:52:45.100
that you're keeping from me?

00:52:47.852 --> 00:52:49.688
Do you mean
regarding Executive Director Oh?

00:52:56.027 --> 00:52:56.903
No, sir.

00:53:15.547 --> 00:53:17.590
Let's see the results of your Swiss trip.

00:53:30.812 --> 00:53:32.814
You couldn't collect the slush fund,
could you?

00:53:33.314 --> 00:53:34.190
How did you know?

00:53:35.150 --> 00:53:38.278
By the way,
did something happen while I was gone?

00:53:38.361 --> 00:53:40.030
I heard Albert and his dad
were kicked out.

00:53:41.948 --> 00:53:44.284
President Shin ended up joining our side,

00:53:44.367 --> 00:53:46.870
and Albert has been
a part of the team for a while now.

00:53:50.665 --> 00:53:53.293
Queen Bee, can I ask you another question?

00:53:53.376 --> 00:53:54.377
What is it?

00:53:54.461 --> 00:53:56.796
What made you
decide to join forces with Ms. Hong?

00:54:03.011 --> 00:54:06.014
I've been beaten up
by all kinds of people since I was a kid.

00:54:07.807 --> 00:54:11.311
By my dad, my brother,
and older classmates at school.

00:54:12.812 --> 00:54:15.523
Sometimes it was with fists,
and other times, it was with words.

00:54:17.734 --> 00:54:21.196
People would look the other way
and walk past as I was being beaten.

00:54:22.447 --> 00:54:24.282
In my 29 years of life,

00:54:24.365 --> 00:54:25.825
no one stepped in to shield me.

00:54:28.078 --> 00:54:29.204
But Jang-mi…

00:54:30.705 --> 00:54:31.873
stepped in every time.

00:54:37.587 --> 00:54:39.547
Well? Are you going to help her?

00:54:39.631 --> 00:54:40.965
Go on. I dare you.

00:54:41.049 --> 00:54:42.592
How dare you try to hit a woman!

00:54:42.675 --> 00:54:43.551
Asshole!

00:54:46.471 --> 00:54:49.432
If you ever run that mouth
about Mi-sook again,

00:54:50.809 --> 00:54:52.268
I will end you.

00:54:52.352 --> 00:54:54.813
She did the same for Mi-sook, not just me.

00:54:55.355 --> 00:54:56.397
So I'm just

00:54:56.981 --> 00:54:58.733
paying back what I owe her
with my talents.

00:55:00.151 --> 00:55:01.736
I always pay my debts,

00:55:01.820 --> 00:55:03.905
and life is all about
"give and take," isn't it?

00:55:16.334 --> 00:55:19.337
You should appoint
Ms. Kang as the president.

00:55:21.256 --> 00:55:24.300
She wouldn't do anything foolish
like Executive Director Oh.

00:55:26.678 --> 00:55:28.888
If Nora becomes president,

00:55:29.514 --> 00:55:33.810
imagine how high and mighty
Choi In-ja will act.

00:55:34.519 --> 00:55:35.478
You know

00:55:36.396 --> 00:55:39.566
she wouldn't cause money problems
like Executive Director Oh did.

00:55:45.572 --> 00:55:47.115
There are times…

00:55:49.951 --> 00:55:52.036
I regret what happened to Myeong-hwi,

00:55:56.166 --> 00:55:58.585
even though it can't be undone.

00:56:01.838 --> 00:56:06.634
Check on the Swiss account
under Nora's name.

00:56:07.802 --> 00:56:11.890
We can't have another incident
like the one with Albert and his father.

00:56:13.683 --> 00:56:15.685
Yes, sir. Of course.

00:56:18.521 --> 00:56:19.522
All right.

00:56:30.909 --> 00:56:32.785
I went to Switzerland,

00:56:32.869 --> 00:56:34.204
and I even made it to the bank,

00:56:35.079 --> 00:56:37.498
but I couldn't withdraw the money.

00:57:07.528 --> 00:57:09.656
He asked if I knew
about the source of the funds.

00:57:10.323 --> 00:57:11.991
You told me last time

00:57:12.867 --> 00:57:15.453
that it was the secret slush fund
my dad kept.

00:57:17.372 --> 00:57:19.958
I got so scared.

00:57:22.335 --> 00:57:24.420
And President Shin also called me.

00:57:25.922 --> 00:57:27.549
He told me that if I was in Switzerland,

00:57:27.632 --> 00:57:29.717
I should come right back
without doing anything.

00:57:30.218 --> 00:57:32.971
He tried hard to stop me
over an international call.

00:57:34.264 --> 00:57:36.432
When did he make that call?

00:57:42.689 --> 00:57:44.691
I understand that you were scared.

00:57:46.192 --> 00:57:49.445
I was also scared when I withdrew
from Hong Jang-mi's account.

00:57:53.032 --> 00:57:54.742
You heard what happened to Big Al, right?

00:57:55.910 --> 00:57:57.996
You might be leaving Director Kang behind

00:57:58.580 --> 00:58:00.290
to become President Kang Nora.

00:58:05.837 --> 00:58:08.047
But I know it too.

00:58:08.590 --> 00:58:12.427
I know I could be kicked out
at any moment, like Albert.

00:58:22.186 --> 00:58:24.814
The Swiss account under Ms. Kang's name

00:58:24.897 --> 00:58:26.274
remains wholly intact.

00:58:26.774 --> 00:58:28.151
That's the balance statement.

00:58:35.408 --> 00:58:36.492
Let's proceed

00:58:37.577 --> 00:58:38.786
with Nora's promotion.

00:58:40.371 --> 00:58:42.332
When the storm hits,

00:58:43.249 --> 00:58:46.252
she could at least
serve as a shield for us.

00:58:54.636 --> 00:58:55.762
LUXURY WOMAN

00:58:56.471 --> 00:58:58.139
HANMIN'S HEIRESS, KANG NORA,
APPOINTED AS PRESIDENT!

00:58:58.222 --> 00:58:59.641
"A NEW ERA IN LEADERSHIP" AT HANMIN

00:59:01.017 --> 00:59:03.144
MS. CHOI DECLINES TO COMMENT
ON RECONCILIATION WITH CHAIRMAN KANG

00:59:03.227 --> 00:59:04.646
HANMIN'S HEIRESS, KANG NORA,
APPOINTED AS PRESIDENT!

00:59:12.779 --> 00:59:14.656
I mean, all I did

00:59:15.239 --> 00:59:17.575
was help put out a promotional article

00:59:17.659 --> 00:59:19.535
for the company and Nora's sake.

00:59:20.161 --> 00:59:22.497
Those reporters threatened me first.

00:59:23.081 --> 00:59:24.582
They said if we didn't go public,

00:59:24.666 --> 00:59:26.709
they would write
about the broken engagement.

00:59:27.293 --> 00:59:30.546
They also squeezed in
that reconciliation talk last minute.

00:59:33.174 --> 00:59:35.718
What exactly were you doing
while you let her do that?

00:59:35.802 --> 00:59:37.136
My apologies, sir.

00:59:37.845 --> 00:59:39.013
It was my oversight.

00:59:42.892 --> 00:59:45.395
Did the reconciliation rumors
rub you the wrong way?

00:59:46.521 --> 00:59:49.107
What's so terrible
about looking like amicable parents

00:59:49.190 --> 00:59:52.026
for the sake of Nora's career
and marriage prospects?

00:59:52.110 --> 00:59:54.404
Am I wrong? What is there to be mad about?

00:59:54.987 --> 00:59:56.656
Just think of it as a simple mistake--

00:59:56.739 --> 00:59:58.032
In my life,

00:59:58.533 --> 01:00:01.369
the biggest mistake
I ever made was you, Choi In-ja.

01:00:01.452 --> 01:00:02.286
What?

01:00:02.370 --> 01:00:05.289
Twenty-six years ago, and even recently,

01:00:05.373 --> 01:00:08.459
you used the kid as an excuse
to get yourself into this house.

01:00:08.543 --> 01:00:11.587
I should've turned you away
and shut you out then.

01:00:13.923 --> 01:00:16.134
Don't you remember
all that parading around…

01:00:18.469 --> 01:00:20.638
eventually got your kid abducted?

01:00:28.020 --> 01:00:29.188
Lie low.

01:00:30.148 --> 01:00:33.484
And refrain from visiting the office
for the time being.

01:00:43.494 --> 01:00:44.328
Damn it.

01:00:46.706 --> 01:00:47.790
{\an8}HORANG AUTO REPAIR SHOP

01:00:52.420 --> 01:00:54.380
HANMIN'S HEIRESS, KANG NORA,
APPOINTED AS PRESIDENT!

01:00:56.299 --> 01:00:58.384
The kid's all grown up.

01:00:59.218 --> 01:01:00.052
She did.

01:01:01.429 --> 01:01:02.805
She even studied abroad?

01:01:18.112 --> 01:01:20.072
{\an8}PRESIDENT KANG NORA

01:01:26.871 --> 01:01:28.164
Congratulations, Ju-ran.

01:01:29.582 --> 01:01:31.626
I saw that article on Kang Nora.

01:01:32.168 --> 01:01:34.587
I'm not the president,
so what is there to celebrate?

01:01:34.670 --> 01:01:35.671
Come on.

01:01:36.214 --> 01:01:38.841
All your in-house enemies are gone.

01:01:39.425 --> 01:01:41.469
It's your world now.

01:01:42.804 --> 01:01:44.889
I'm not as happy as I thought I'd be.

01:01:47.225 --> 01:01:51.145
The chairman also yelled at Madam Choi
over that article this morning.

01:01:52.605 --> 01:01:56.192
Maybe it's because
there's still a lingering threat?

01:01:59.946 --> 01:02:01.197
Hey, Ms. Song.

01:02:01.280 --> 01:02:02.365
You're already here.

01:02:03.866 --> 01:02:06.619
I see you still came,
despite what the chairman said.

01:02:06.702 --> 01:02:09.872
I couldn't just let my kid go alone
on a day like this.

01:02:10.373 --> 01:02:12.166
We just need to keep it a secret from him.

01:02:12.250 --> 01:02:14.710
Officially, Choi In-ja is lying low.

01:02:19.215 --> 01:02:21.259
Welcome, President Kang.

01:02:22.844 --> 01:02:23.719
"President Kang."

01:02:25.471 --> 01:02:26.973
Let's go and take that seat.

01:02:29.517 --> 01:02:30.351
Here we go.

01:02:30.935 --> 01:02:31.811
President Kang.

01:02:37.692 --> 01:02:39.277
My goodness.

01:02:41.529 --> 01:02:43.698
That seat was made for you.

01:02:47.243 --> 01:02:48.119
Ms. Song.

01:02:48.744 --> 01:02:50.955
You know you have to do
even better now, right?

01:02:55.585 --> 01:02:56.878
I'll give it my all

01:02:56.961 --> 01:02:59.046
to serve you
to the best of my abilities, ma'am.

01:03:02.174 --> 01:03:03.050
"Ma'am."

01:03:12.101 --> 01:03:13.102
It's so good.

01:03:15.271 --> 01:03:17.815
People would think you owned this house.

01:03:17.899 --> 01:03:20.568
They'd know he's a freeloader
with one look.

01:03:22.445 --> 01:03:23.738
I gave up my five percent,

01:03:23.821 --> 01:03:26.115
so you could at least provide
room and board.

01:03:26.616 --> 01:03:27.617
All right.

01:03:27.700 --> 01:03:29.368
As of today,

01:03:29.452 --> 01:03:32.663
Yeouido Pirates has amassed
19% of Hanmin's shares to become

01:03:32.747 --> 01:03:34.457
the second-largest shareholder.

01:03:36.292 --> 01:03:39.211
We'll shift our shareholding purpose
from passive investment

01:03:39.295 --> 01:03:41.380
to active involvement in management.

01:03:50.348 --> 01:03:52.850
YEOUIDO PIRATES DECLARES INTENT
TO PARTICIPATE IN HANMIN'S MANAGEMENT

01:03:52.934 --> 01:03:55.519
{\an8}KANG PIL-BEOM, HONG KEUM-BO

01:03:56.228 --> 01:03:57.355
My head tells me…

01:03:57.939 --> 01:03:59.023
KANG PIL-BEOM

01:03:59.106 --> 01:04:00.274
…to join this side.

01:04:02.360 --> 01:04:03.361
But my heart…

01:04:04.987 --> 01:04:06.030
HONG KEUM-BO

01:04:06.113 --> 01:04:07.782
…tells me to join that side.

01:04:20.670 --> 01:04:22.713
So you're saying

01:04:22.797 --> 01:04:27.843
that Albert and Hong Keum-bo
are partners right now.

01:04:27.927 --> 01:04:28.761
Yes, sir.

01:04:29.720 --> 01:04:31.347
This is Hong Keum-bo's profile.

01:04:31.931 --> 01:04:34.767
- Goodness.
- She's a 35-year-old woman.

01:04:34.850 --> 01:04:36.310
Up until last December,

01:04:36.394 --> 01:04:39.772
she was a Capital Market Investigator
at the Financial Supervisory Service.

01:04:41.190 --> 01:04:42.817
The FSS?

01:04:44.235 --> 01:04:48.406
She was a part of the probe
into Hanmin's slush fund last July.

01:04:51.158 --> 01:04:51.993
Is that so?

01:04:52.076 --> 01:04:54.286
That must be why

01:04:54.912 --> 01:04:57.123
Albert asked about Myeong-hwi.

01:04:57.707 --> 01:04:58.958
We should start

01:04:59.041 --> 01:05:01.752
by looking into her intent
on attacking our company--

01:05:01.836 --> 01:05:03.671
No, not that.

01:05:03.754 --> 01:05:05.631
The intent is not important.

01:05:06.424 --> 01:05:10.928
What's important
is where she got that money.

01:05:16.058 --> 01:05:17.226
You dare interrupt a meeting?

01:05:17.309 --> 01:05:18.352
I'm sorry, ma'am.

01:05:19.812 --> 01:05:21.063
Mr. Shin Jung-woo

01:05:21.814 --> 01:05:23.858
is on the line,
hoping to speak to the chairman.

01:05:23.941 --> 01:05:25.151
Shin Jung-woo?

01:05:25.234 --> 01:05:27.611
He says he's representing Yeouido Pirates.

01:05:28.195 --> 01:05:29.613
What did you just say?

01:05:33.034 --> 01:05:34.035
Shin Jung-woo.

01:05:34.869 --> 01:05:39.623
I never thought I'd be
calling out your name again so soon.

01:05:39.707 --> 01:05:41.125
Things turned out that way.

01:05:41.208 --> 01:05:43.127
I'm calling on behalf
of our CEO, Ms. Hong.

01:05:44.712 --> 01:05:45.880
Why you little…

01:05:46.464 --> 01:05:48.841
You must be curious about
where we got the funds

01:05:48.924 --> 01:05:50.134
to purchase Hanmin stocks.

01:05:50.217 --> 01:05:51.594
Yes, of course!

01:05:51.677 --> 01:05:54.847
That's what I'm most curious about.

01:05:54.930 --> 01:05:57.308
I faxed a list of our funding sources
to the 12th floor.

01:05:57.850 --> 01:05:59.435
Feel free to check for yourself.

01:06:01.395 --> 01:06:03.105
Bring me the fax that just came in.

01:06:16.077 --> 01:06:18.871
HANMIN'S SLUSH FUND DETAILS

01:06:21.499 --> 01:06:22.541
Zero balance?

01:06:23.793 --> 01:06:24.794
Zero?

01:06:25.294 --> 01:06:26.170
What on earth…

01:06:27.338 --> 01:06:28.964
How the hell did this happen?

01:06:29.465 --> 01:06:32.301
What the hell happened here?

01:06:35.679 --> 01:06:36.931
CURRENT BALANCE: 0 WON

01:06:38.390 --> 01:06:40.059
JOGEOK BANK
CERTIFICATE OF ACCOUNT BALANCE

01:06:47.441 --> 01:06:51.153
That's the list of borrowed-name accounts
of branch managers and their families

01:06:51.237 --> 01:06:52.863
that Hanmin used to hide slush funds.

01:06:55.491 --> 01:06:57.785
Our CEO wanted me
to thank you on her behalf.

01:06:58.285 --> 01:06:59.703
Thank you for the funds.

01:07:07.920 --> 01:07:11.423
Goddamn it!

01:07:17.304 --> 01:07:18.264
Damn it.

01:07:21.934 --> 01:07:23.602
I spoke to Chairman Kang

01:07:23.686 --> 01:07:26.438
and told him that his slush funds
were the source of our funds.

01:07:27.022 --> 01:07:30.192
Now that he knows they're gone,
he won't sit idly by.

01:07:38.284 --> 01:07:40.077
HONG KEUM-BO

01:07:44.915 --> 01:07:45.833
{\an8}CHAIRMAN KANG PIL-BEOM

01:07:45.916 --> 01:07:46.959
{\an8}Albert.

01:07:48.961 --> 01:07:50.296
Shin Jung-woo.

01:07:52.381 --> 01:07:54.008
Hong Keum-bo.

01:07:57.052 --> 01:07:58.554
You were foolish enough

01:08:00.055 --> 01:08:02.057
to steal what belongs to me.

01:08:04.560 --> 01:08:06.979
Now you must pay the price.

01:08:20.284 --> 01:08:22.119
ULLALA CHICKEN

01:09:12.962 --> 01:09:14.797
{\an8}UNDERCOVER MISS HONG

01:09:15.673 --> 01:09:17.299
{\an8}Yeouido Pirates hereby declares its intent

01:09:17.383 --> 01:09:21.470
{\an8}to formally participate in the management
of Hanmin Investment & Securities.

01:09:21.553 --> 01:09:22.846
{\an8}How is it at the office?

01:09:22.930 --> 01:09:25.474
{\an8}The company morale is at an all-time low.

01:09:25.975 --> 01:09:28.018
{\an8}This should be enough
to go up against Chairman Kang.

01:09:28.102 --> 01:09:30.646
{\an8}Are you seriously suggesting that
as an option right now?

01:09:31.230 --> 01:09:33.691
{\an8}He gave the order
to withdraw the VIP's slush fund.

01:09:33.774 --> 01:09:35.359
{\an8}Are we sure we can touch that?

01:09:35.442 --> 01:09:37.403
{\an8}We have to do everything we can right now.

01:09:37.486 --> 01:09:39.196
{\an8}Why would I betray the chairman?

01:09:39.280 --> 01:09:40.781
{\an8}We need you to take a stand.

01:09:40.864 --> 01:09:42.074
{\an8}What is the agenda item

01:09:42.157 --> 01:09:45.452
{\an8}the Pirates want to raise
at the shareholders' meeting?

01:09:45.536 --> 01:09:47.454
{\an8}The removal of Chairman Kang Pil-beom.

01:09:48.706 --> 01:09:53.711
{\an8}Subtitle translation by: Justin S. Kim